The paper presents a deep learning-based solution for segmenting both white matter lesions and deep grey matter structures in magnetic resonance imaging in multiple sclerosis. This involves image analysis and computer vision techniques, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the comparison of the method with human raters, which involves human-computer interaction and human-centered computing, falling under the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
